positive feedback in my Practicum I course and maintain a 3.97 GPA. I am organized, proactive, and attentive to detail, particularly when it comes to clinical documentation and follow-through.\n\nMy background includes leadership experience in the US Navy and in the construction industry, which strengthened my communication skills, adaptability, and ability to work independently and collaboratively. I am also comfortable with technology and learning new systems.\n\nRegarding availability, I am seeking to begin Practicum II in the Summer 2026 semester (5/18/26 – 8/7/26), with the intention of continuing into Internship in Fall 2026 (8/24/26 – 12/11/26), which typically spans two semesters.\n\nThank you very much for your time and consideration.\n\nBest Regards,\nZachary Melman"
